module-collision is complete, simulates impacts having any 1D Constitutive with sliding and static friction having a friction coefficient as a function of velocity for each of N-pairs of collision bodies within a collision world. The module is available at _____, and a demonstration video is available at _____.

For mbdyn v1.7, the accompanying patch to rodj is required.

libBullet must also be installed.

For Debian and for Ubuntu, the following configuration line works.

./configure --enable-runtime-loading --with-module="inline_friction collision" LDFLAGS="-rdynamic -lBulletSoftBody -lBulletDynamics -lBulletCollision -lLinearMath" CPPFLAGS=-I/usr/include/bullet

